{
  "texts": [
    "Despite their booming performance there are some challenges to be considered when utilizing attentions or transformers in case of very large volumes of data: (1) Computational Cost: Transformers heavily rely on attention mechanisms, which involve comparing every element in the input sequence to each other.",
    "This leads to quadratic complexity, meaning their computational cost grows with the square of the data size.",
    "While techniques like sparse attention and efficient implementations can alleviate this issue, it still remains a hurdle for extremely large datasets.",
    "(2) Memory Bottlenecks: Processing entire large datasets at once might not be possible due to memory limitations.",
    "Transformers usually need the entire input sequence in memory for attention calculations, making handling massive datasets in a single batch challenging."
  ]
}